h3. Issue Summary
The following article: [Aligning release dates|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jiraportfolioserver/aligning-release-dates-967895282.html] is displaying incomplete information.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Open the article.
 # Navigate until the bottom of the article until you locate the following section:
{quote}
(I) You need the Advanced Roadmaps user permission to save changes in Jira Software.
{quote}

h3. Expected Results

The information displayed is correct:
{quote}
(I) You need the *Advanced Roadmaps user* permission to save changes in Jira Software. Additionally, you will need the *Administer Projects* permission in all projects associated with the *cross-project release*.
{quote}

h3. Actual Results

Incomplete information is displayed instead:

{quote}
(I) You need the Advanced Roadmaps user permission to save changes in Jira Software.
{quote}

h3. Workaround

 Currently, there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary
"Select this and all descendant issues" option selects even issues not in view

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a new plan;
# Create a issue in hierarchy from Epic to Sub-task;
# Change the hierarchy scope from Epic to Story (to effectively hide sub-tasks away);
# From the epic, click *... > Select this and all descendant issues*;
# Attempt to bulk change issues and verify that Sprint and Teams are disabled;

h3. Expected Results
The feature only selects issues that are visible. Since we are going from Epic to Story, it should not select sub-tasks;

h3. Actual Results
The feature also select hidden issues;

h3. Workaround
# Filter all issues you want to bulk change using the filter options;
# Select them all using the top check box;
# Bulk change as desired;

Ideally, we want Jira auto-syncs the Program whenever the page is opened/refreshed (like they do with Jira Plans). At a minimum we should be able to set an auto-sync interval (e.g. daily sync) to ensure the Program never gets too outdated.
h3. Workaround: 
While not a true workaround there is a way to script a REST API to sync a program: 
{code:java}
curl --location --request POST 'BASEURL/jira858/rest/jpo/1.0/programs/calculate' \--header 'Authorization: Basic xxxxxxxxx' \--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \--data-raw '{"programId":1}' {code}
You'll need to know the program ID, it can be gleaned from the URL when loading the program.
